 indicate that H_\\kappa\\\nprovides a non-superintegrable generalization of H. We compare this result with\na previously known superintegrable curved analogue H'_\\kappa\\ of the 1:2\nEuclidean oscillator showing that the \\Omega=3\\delta\\ specialization of\nH_\\kappa\\ does not coincide with H'_\\kappa. Finally, the geometrical\ninterpretation of the curved \"centrifugal\" terms appearing in H_\\kappa\\ is also\ndiscussed in detail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 30 Jun 2012 10:13:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 Feb 2013 12:03:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
